comment.body:
Developer here. Stumbled upon this post on 'Everyone' feed. Pleasantly surprised, and glad to hear that you're enjoying it. Hope you don't mind my barging in!

> Do I have to create my own gallery hub to be able to upload?

@ulrichard: Yes, so that no one could have control over your content, but you. I believe it is the way a decenteralized web should behave in, so currently there is no plan to support sharing a gallery hub "officially". Of course, the site itself does not care about ideologies as long as the data files are there, so you can use some other mechanism to achieve that. e.g. ZeroNet's multiple signers

> the image title between Prev and Back links to the raw image address, though it may be better that it's (also) on the top
>
> it may be better that the info panel of photo is in the bottom or able to hide/expand

@Binchan: Nice ideas! Links on both ends should be more convienent, and making the info panel hidden while viewing large images likely won't hurt. Should be easy enough. Looking into implementing them once I fix my build system.

> I need to scroll image or change zoom to view it full.

@ZAlex: Are you on a phone? I was lazy and haven't gone responsive yet, but in case of a missing `viewport`, phone browsers should be scaling the page down until it fits. Text would be small but image viewing should mostly be fine. Not sure what's happening there, but I guess the proper solution is making it fully responsive some day.
